  <h2><a href="../../blog-posts/how-does-chinas-12th-five-year-plan-address-energy-and-environment" title="How does China‚Äôs 12th Five-Year Plan address energy and the environment?">How does China‚Äôs 12th Five-Year Plan address energy and the environment?</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Posted by Deborah Seligsohn and Angel Hsu on Mar 7, 2011</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/4407552795_4083101675.jpg" alt="" title="" width="160" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>The draft of China‚Äôs much-anticipated 12th Five-Year Plan was released this Saturday, March 5 at the opening session of the National People‚Äôs Congress (NPC).  The Plan will actually be brought to a vote at the close of the session later this week. While there may be some changes to the Plan, in past years these have not been large.</p>
  </div>
<div class="clear-block">
    	<div class="readmore"> <a href="../../blog-posts/how-does-chinas-12th-five-year-plan-address-energy-and-environment">Read more</a> </div>
